@sppeterson @francis_scarr The more complex a system, the more humans try to simplify it (for often very understandable reasons).
This unfortunately tends to strip out redundancy and causes the system to become more brittle / less adaptive.
Which types of present-day societies will still exist in 2122?

@DublinReader @KiarKini @francis_scarr @KevinRothrock Exactly!
Complex systems, whether social, economic, biologic, or technologic (e.g. the Challenger disaster) often fail in ways impossible to predict (even given perfect info).
Since they have in-built redundancies, when they do fail, they tend to fail in a catastrophic manner.

